 for bestpractices and # Company Selection & Time Window Controls

## Overview
Build a cohesive, enterprise-grade feature set that enables users to search, select, and persist companies, paired with flexible time-window controls to drive the Investor Perception Index (IPI) workflows. The system should deliver a fast, accessible, and explainable experience: debounced autocomplete with fuzzy matching, recent/saved companies per user, predefined time-window presets plus a customizable range, and robust safety guards for data handling. The feature set powers two key pages: a Dashboard (primary authenticated landing) and a Company View (IPI Detail) with drill-down capability to answer “Why did this move?”.

## Components to Build

- CompanySelector
  - Purpose: Searchable company picker with auto-complete, recent/saved companies, keyboard navigation, and accessible ARIA roles.
  - Tech: Debounced input, fuzzy matching, typeahead suggestions, pagination for suggestions, per-user cached recents.
  - Data: Ticker, name, exchange, metadata (industry, region), current IPI anchor if available.
  - Behaviors:
    - Debounce input ~250ms; fetch suggestions with query, page, and limit.
    - Show top N suggestions with highlight for matched substring.
    - Allow keyboard navigation (Arrow Up/Down), Enter selects; Escape closes.
    - Persist recent selections locally and on server (per user) with a "Recent" section.
    - Allow saving a company to “Saved” or to a user’s portfolio with a single action; reflect saved state instantly.
  - Safety: Guard all array operations with Array.isArray(results) and use data ?? [] from API calls.

- TimeWindowControls
  - Purpose: Provide preset ranges and a custom date/time range, synchronizing with IPI calculations.
  - Presets: 1D, 1W, 1M, 3M, YTD, 1Y, All (with sensible defaults).
  - Custom range:
    - Start Date/End Date pickers with validation (start <= end, within allowed bounds).
    - Quick toggle to apply or clear range.
  - UI: Clear, apply, and reset controls; show current range in summary chip(s).
  - Accessibility: keyboard accessible date inputs; appropriate ARIA labels.

- Dashboard (page_core_006)
  - Summary: Authenticated landing page where users select a company and time window, view saved companies, and see IPI quick-summaries.
  - Widgets:
    - Left/Top: CompanySelector with recent and saved indicators.
    - Right/Main: IPI quick-summary cards (current value, directional change arrow up/down, timestamp) per selected company and range.
    - Saved Companies Shelf: horizontally scrollable or grid-based gallery of saved companies with quick actions (select, remove).
    - Drill-down entry points: "Why did this move?" CTA per IPI summary.
  - Data flow: On company select or time window change, fetch and display:
    - Current IPI value and direction
    - Top narratives or placeholders if not enough data
    - Lightweight timeline snippet or sparkline
  - Performance: Prefetch commonly accessed company data; cache recent results per user.

- Company View (IPI Detail) (page_core_007)
  - Purpose: Detail view for the selected company showing current IPI, directional change, top 3 narratives, timeline, and CTA to delve into 'Why did this move?'.
  - Layout:
    - Hero card: Company name, ticker, and current IPI with directional indicator.
    - Top Narratives: 3 cards/list items with short summaries and provenance chips.
    - Timeline: Horizontal/vertical timeline of events contributing to the move; interactive markers.
    - Drill-down CTA: "Why did this move?" opens a detailed drill-down panel or navigates to a dedicated drill-down view with underlying events.
  - Data: IPI current value, direction, contributing events with sources; raw payloads for audit.
  - Accessibility: keyboard navigable timeline; screen reader friendly labeling.

- API/Backend Integration
  - Endpoints to support:
    - GET /api/companies/suggest?query=...&page=...&limit=... (with debounced, paginated suggestions)
    - GET /api/companies/recent (per-user recent)
    - POST /api/companies/save (save a company to user profile)
    - GET /api/ipi/current?companyId=...&start=...&end=... (IPI summary for range)
    - GET /api/ipi/details?companyId=...&start=...&end=... (top narratives, timeline)
  - Data shape handling:
    - Always validate: const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : [];
    - Use data ?? [] for any fetch results that could be null.
  - Performance: server-side caching for frequent company suggestions; per-user cache for recent results.

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Debounced Autocomplete
  - Debounce input to ~250ms.
  - Typeahead with fuzzy matching for name/ticker.
  - Guard all results: const suggestions = (data?.suggestions ?? []) as Array<Suggestion>.
  - Render: ranked suggestions with matched substring highlighting; show ticker and name; include optional industry.
  - Pagination: support next/previous page via API; render controls with ARIA attributes.
  - Keyboard: navigate suggestions with arrows, select with Enter, clear with Esc.
  - Accessibility: ARIA roles for list, option, and listbox; announce updates to screen readers.

- Company Cards & Saved State
  - Represent saved/unsaved status; toggle with optimistic UI update.
  - Persist saved state on backend; fallback to local cache if offline.
  - Input validation: sanitize any user-provided company identifiers before usage.

- TimeWindowControls
  - Implement presets with clear labels and numeric ranges.
  - Custom range inputs with validation and error messaging.
  - Persist selected range to UI state and pass to IPI fetch calls.

- Dashboard & Company View Pages
  - Use a shared, well-typed data layer with strict PropTypes/TypeScript interfaces.
  - Ensure all array operations guard against null/undefined: (items ?? []).map(...), Array.isArray(items) ? items.map(...) : [].
  - Use useState<T[]>([]) for any array state; initialize with empty arrays.
  - Data loading states: skeletons or placeholders during fetch; error states with retry.
  - Drilling into "Why did this move?" navigates to a detail panel or route with preserved state.
  - All charts, timelines, and narrative lists adhere to the design system and accessibility guidelines.

### Backend
- Database & Search
  - Tables: companies(id, ticker, name, exchange, metadata JSONB, created_at, updated_at)
  - Full-text search index: tsvector on name, ticker, alias fields for fast suggestions.
  - API: endpoints for suggestions, recent, save actions; ensure input validation and sanitization to prevent injection.
  - Results: Always return data in shapes expected by frontend; use null-safe patterns.

- Ingestion & Safety
  - Implement ingestion endpoints for external signals (news/social/earnings transcripts) as per MVP; ensure idempotency and retry logic.
  - Audit: persist raw payloads for each event; ensure immutable write-once semantics for canonical narrative events.

### Integration
- State Management
  - Centralized data layer sharing: Company data, IPI state, and time window selections propagated to dashboard and detail views.
  - Ensure that selecting a company or time window triggers dependent data fetches (IPI, narratives, timelines) consistently.

- Error Handling
  - Graceful fallbacks for missing data: display empty-state messages with guidance.
  - Retry policies with exponential backoff for transient backend errors.

- Security
  - Authenticated endpoints; protect company data and user-specific saves.
  - Input validation and escaping on both client and server sides.
  - Use per-user access tokens or session-based auth as per project conventions.

## User Experience Flow

- Entry
  - User lands on Dashboard (page_core_006) after login.
  - The top area presents CompanySelector (with a “Recent” and “Saved” sections) and TimeWindowControls (predefined presets and a custom range button).
  - The main area shows a current IPI quick-summary for the selected company and range, plus a Saved Companies shelf.

- Interactions
  - User types in CompanySelector; autocomplete suggestions appear; user selects a company via keyboard or mouse.
  - User toggles time-window presets or defines a custom range; the IPI quick-summary updates in real-time.
  - User clicks on a saved company to quickly switch to that company and range state.
  - User clicks to drill down: “Why did this move?” → navigates to Company View (IPI Detail) showing current IPI, direction, top 3 narratives, and a timeline.
  - User can read details and use the drill-down again to explore underlying events.

- Edge Cases
  - No results for a query: show friendly empty state with tips to broaden search.
  - Large company lists: paginate suggestions; ensure performance under 100k–unbounded indices.
  - Network hiccups: show retry actions and cached results when offline.

## Technical Specifications

- Data Models
  - Company:
    - id: UUID
    - ticker: string
    - name: string
    - exchange: string
    - metadata: JSONB
    - createdAt: timestamp
    - updatedAt: timestamp
  - SavedCompany (User-specific):
    - userId: UUID
    - companyId: UUID
    - savedAt: timestamp
  - RecentCompany (per-user cache / session):
    - userId: UUID
    - companyId: UUID
    - lastViewed: timestamp
  - IPIResult:
    - companyId: UUID
    - windowStart: date
    - windowEnd: date
    - value: float
    - direction: 'up'|'down'|'flat'
    - updatedAt: timestamp
  - NarrativeEvent:
    - id: UUID
    - companyId: UUID
    - source: string
    - speaker: string
    - audience: string
    - rawText: text
    - timestamp: timestamp
    - payload: JSONB

- API Endpoints
  - GET /api/companies/suggest?query=&page=&limit=
  - GET /api/companies/recent
  - POST /api/companies/save (companyId, action=save|unsave)
  - GET /api/ipi/current?companyId=&start=&end=
  - GET /api/ipi/details?companyId=&start=&end=
  - GET /api/ipi/timeline?companyId=&start=&end=
  - GET /api/auth/me (for user identity, if needed)

- Security
  - JWT-based or session-auth for API requests.
  - Validate all inputs on server: query strings, IDs, dates.
  - Escape/serialize all user-generated content before rendering.

- Validation
  - Debounce and throttle input to prevent abuse.
  - Ensure date range validation on client and server; reject invalid ranges with clear messages.
  - Validate array shapes and required fields before mapping/computations.

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Autocomplete: Debounced search returns suggestions within ~150ms for typical 100k+ company sets; suggestions render with accurate highlighting and keyboard navigation.
- [ ] Safety: All array-like results are guarded: (items ?? []).map(...) and Array.isArray(items) ? items.map(...) : [] across UI layers.
- [ ] State defaults: All array states are initialized with useState<Type[]>([]) in React components.
- [ ] Data integrity: API responses validated server-side; client handles missing data gracefully without crashes.
- [ ] UX: Time window presets function correctly; custom range is validated; saved and recent sections persist and reflect updates instantly.
- [ ] Dashboard: Current IPI value, direction, and top narratives render for the selected company and range; loading and error states are graceful.
- [ ] Drill-down: “Why did this move?” navigates to IPI Detail with correct context and underlying events.
- [ ] Accessibility: All interactive elements are keyboard accessible; ARIA roles assigned to lists, listitems, and combobox; focus-visible styling present.

## UI/UX Guidelines
Apply the project's design system:
- Use the defined color palette and typography tokens.
- Maintain card-based surfaces with subtle borders and soft shadows.
- Ensure clear visual hierarchy: large numerals for IPI values, readable metadata, and distinct narrative chips.
- Favor restrained motion: slide/fade transitions for panels, ~180ms durations.
- Prioritize fast scannability, enterprise polish, and explainable UI cues (provenance chips, raw payloads, and drill-down affordances).
- Ensure accessible contrast and focus states across all interactive elements.

---

## Visual Style
(See provided visual style guidelines in the prompt for exact tokens. Implement UI components that strictly adhere to these colors, typography, spacing, and element treatments.)

- Color Palette, Typography, Spacing, and Card/Navigation guidelines must be implemented as described.
- Data Visualization should be minimalistic: clean lines, light grids, and neutral background surfaces with accent signals for IPI direction and narratives.

---

## Mandatory Coding Standards — Runtime Safety

CRITICAL: Follow these rules in ALL generated code to prevent runtime crashes.

1. Supabase query results:
   - Always use nullish coalescing — const items = data ?? [].
2. Array methods (.map, .filter, .reduce, etc.):
   - Never call on a value that could be null/undefined/non-array.
   - Guard with (items ?? []).map(...) or Array.isArray(items) ? items.map(...) : [].
3. React useState for arrays/objects:
   - Always initialize with the correct type — useState<Type[]>([]) for arrays.
4. API response shapes:
   - Always validate — const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : [].
5. Optional chaining:
   - Use obj?.property?.nested when accessing nested API responses or DB results.
6. Destructuring with defaults:
   - const { items = [], count = 0 } = response ?? {}.

